			<div id='header'>
				<img src='../aux/icon64_2.png' class='headerIcon' />
				<h1>Outline Tracker Screen Shots</h1>
				<p>The leading task list manager for HP webOS!</p>
			</div>

			<div class='onlyif1col'>
				<a href='#nav'>Zum Menü springen</a>
			</div>

			<div id='main'>
				<div id='content'>
					<div class='floatright300'><img src='visuals/outline_vehicle.png' width='320' height='480' alt='project outline' /></div>
					<p>Organize your projects into tasks and sub-tasks as many layers deep as you need.  Add notes to tasks or tasks to notes.  Whether you work top-down, bottom-up, or inside-out, Outline Tracker works with you.</p>
					<p>Outline items can be collapsed to show the big picture, or expanded to show detail.</p>

					<p class='clearboth'> </p>
					<div class='floatright300'><img src='visuals/to-do_home.png' width='320' height='480' alt='dynamic to-do scene' /></div>
					<p>Select the Place you're at, and the dynamic to-do scene shows only the tasks you can work on here and now.
					Today's tasks are hilighted in yellow; past-due tasks in red.
					The color-coded checkbox shows at a glance who's responsible for a task -- you, your organization, or no one.  Tasks are organized by project.</p>

					<p class='clearboth'> </p>
					<div class='floatright300'><img src='visuals/by_due_date.png' width='320' height='480' alt='dynamic By Due Date list' /></div>
					<p>Switch to the <strong>Nach Datum</strong> scene to see upcoming tasks and events.</p>
					<p>These items also appear in the webOS Calendar (see below).</p>

					<p class='clearboth'> </p>
					<div class='floatright300'><img src='visuals/waiting.png' width='480' height='320' alt='dynamic waiting list' /></div>
					<p>The dynamic waiting list shows tasks that are waiting for action by someone else, organized by person. Tapping a person's name takes you to his or her entry in the webOS Contacts application, where you can phone, e-mail or instant message him or her.</p>

					<p class='clearboth'> </p>
					<div class='floatright300'><img src='visuals/places.png' width='320' height='480' alt='places scene' /></div>
					<p>A Place can represent a physical place, like your home, or a context like “botengänge machen”.  Places are independent of projects, so when you're running errands, you can see tasks for your job and your personal life.</p>
					<p>Places can include other Places.  Here, the place “Geschäftlich” includes the place “Desktop Rechner”. When you're at work, you'll see tasks that require a desktop computer, but if you're at a computer elsewhere, you won't see your work tasks.</p>

					<p class='clearboth'> </p>
					<div class='floatright300'><img src='visuals/details.png' width='320' height='480' alt='details scene' /></div>
					<p>Keep track of where you can work on a task, who's responsible and when it's due.</p>
					<p>Items with a Fälligkeitsdatum will appear in the webOS Calendar (see below).</p>

					<p class='clearboth'> </p>
					<div class='floatright300'><img src='visuals/card_view.png' width='320' height='480' alt='card view of Outline Tracker' /></div>
					<p>Use card view to switch between the dynamic to-do list and project cards.</p>
					<p>Add a new tasks or notes quickly (even if Outline Tracker isn't open) using Einfach Lostippen. (requires webOS 2.x or 3.x)</p>

					<p class='clearboth'> </p>
					<div class='floatright300'><img src='visuals/calendar.png' width='320' height='480' alt='Outline Tracker items in webOS Calendar' /></div>
					<p>Outline Tracker items with a date appear in the webOS Calendar. Completed tasks show a checkmark, incomplete tasks an empty box and notes have neither.</p>
					<p>By default, completed tasks are not shown &mdash; preferences allow you to show top-level tasks, lower-level tasks, or both.</p>

					<p class='clearboth'> </p>
					<div class='floatright300'><img src='visuals/searchable_faq.png' width='320' height='480' alt='searchable FAQ' /></div>
					<p>Search the FAQ (accessed from the Help scene) for tips and techniques on a subject.</p>

					<p class='clearboth'> </p>
					<div class='floatright300'><img src='visuals/content_text.png' width='320' height='480' alt='content text' /></div>
					<p>Content text lets you add notes to an item, without cluttering the dynamic to-do list or Outline scene.
					In an outline scene, tap the knobs to show or hide.
					In the dynamic to-do list, just rotate your handheld!</p>

 					<p class='clearboth'> </p>
					<div class='floatright300'><img src='visuals/tp_outline_crop480.png' width='480' height='797' /></div>
					<p>Outline Tracker uses the full screen height on tablets.</p>
